##  Reflection: What I Learned

Writing an SAR forces clarity and accountability. Itâ€™s one thing to assess controls â€” itâ€™s another to explain them in a way that leadership understands and acts on. I found it especially challenging to **balance technical precision with executive clarity**.

For instance, itâ€™s easy to say â€œRDS wasnâ€™t encrypted,â€ but much harder to explain why thatâ€™s a **moderate risk** and what the implications could be for patient data.

This exercise reminded me that **GRC work lives in the details** â€” but decision-makers live in the summary. We must serve both.

